          optyn.com Privacy Policy
        %div
          %p
            %strong Updated February 1, 2013
          %p
            This privacy policy (the "Privacy Policy") describes how Optyn uses and protects any
            information that you give us when you use this Site and Services. Optyn is committed to
            ensuring that your privacy is protected. Should we ask you to provide certain information
            by which you can be identified ("Personal Information") when using this Site, then you can
            be assured that it will only be used in accordance with this Privacy Policy.  In addition,
            this Privacy Policy addresses how we treat information that is not associated with or
            linked to your Personal Information and which does not permit you to be identified
            ("Statistical Information").
          %p
            %strong Your Consent
          %p
            When you access or use Optyn’s Site and Services, you agree to the terms and conditions of
            this Privacy Policy, which is incorporated into and forms a part of Optyn’s Terms of Use
            (set forth on http://www.optyn.com/terms). You expressly consent to the processing of your
            Personal Information and Statistical Information according to this Privacy Policy.
          %p
            %strong Policy Toward Children
          %p
            Children between the ages of 13 and 18 should only use the Site and Services with the
            permission and supervision of their parent or guardian.  Children under 13 years of age are
            not permitted to use the Site or Services.  If we become aware that a user is under 13 and
            we unknowingly collected Personal Information, we will remove that user's Personal Information
            permanently from our records.
          %p
            %strong Collection of Personal Information
          %p
            Any and all Personal Information such as name, address and email, that you provide in
            connection with your use of the Site or Services is collected by us.  It is collected in
            order that we may deliver a more personalized service or facilitate the purchase of a Deal
            or some other activity.  When you contact us by email we collect your email address.  We may
            also collect information about you from any social network or merchant from which you may have
            connected to the Site.  Personal Information may also be received about you from other sources
            with which you have registered and with whom we have partnered.  We may associate the
            information we receive with the Personal Information you have provided to us.
          %p
            %strong Statistical Information
          %p
            We create records from Personal Information and delete any information that will enable
            the information to be personally identifiable to you (the “Statistical Information”).
            Statistical Information is aggregated this used in statistical analysis to help us analyze
            patterns in the use of the Site and the Services.
          %p
            This Privacy Policy does not limit our use or disclosure of any Statistical Information
            in any way, and we reserve the right to use and disclose Statistical Information to our
            partners, advertisers and other third parties in our discretion.
          %p
            %strong Information Collection
          %p
            A cookie ("Cookie") is a small file which asks permission to be placed on your computer's
            hard drive. Once you agree, the file is added and the Cookie helps analyze web traffic or
            lets you know when you visit a particular site.  Cookies allow web applications to respond
            to you as an individual.  The web application can tailor its operations to your needs, likes
            and dislikes by gathering and remembering information about your preferences.
          %p
            We use traffic log Cookies to identify which pages are being used. This helps us analyze
            data about web page traffic and improve our website in order to tailor it to customer needs.
            We only use this information for statistical analysis purposes and then the data is removed
            from the system.
          %p
            Overall, Cookies help us provide you with a better website, by enabling us to monitor
            which pages you find useful and which you do not. A Cookie in no way gives us access to
            your computer or any information about you, other than the data you choose to share with us.
          %p
            You can choose to accept or decline Cookies. Most web browsers automatically accept cookies,
            but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline Cookies if you prefer. This may
            prevent you from taking full advantage of the Site.
          %p
            An "Internet Protocol Address" or "IP Address" is a number that is automatically assigned
            to your computer when you use the Internet.  Optyn, or our service providers, may track your
            IP Address when you access the Site to assist with targeting advertising and notices to you.
          %p
            We may also allow advertisers to promote third-party products and/or services by placing
            advertisements on Optyn. These advertisers may use Cookies and/or "Web Beacons" (which are
            usually small, transparent graphic images) in order to monitor information related to the
            advertiser’s promotion. Clicking on an advertiser’s promotion will direct you to the website
            of a third-party and the advertiser. This Privacy Policy does not cover the privacy practices
            of any advertisers.
          %p
            %strong Use and Disclosure of Information
          %p
            Except as otherwise stated in this Privacy Policy, we do not sell, trade, rent, or otherwise
            share for marketing purposes the Personal Information that we collect with third parties,
            unless you ask or authorize us to do so.
          %p
            In general, Personal Information you submit to us is used by us to better understand your
            needs and provide you with a better service, and in particular for the following reasons:
          %ul
            %li Internal record keeping.
            %li
              To send promotional email about new products, special offers or other information
              which we think you may find interesting using the email address which you have provided.
            %li
              From time to time, we may also use your Personal Information to contact you for market
              research purposes.
            %li We may use Personal Information to customize the website according to your interests.
            %li
              We may provide your information to our third party partners who work on our behalf to
              provide some of the services and features we present on the Site.
          %p
            We may share your Personal Information with Optyn affiliated companies that are under a
            common control.  In such cases, the affiliates will we will honor this Privacy Policy.
          %p
            In the event that Optyn is part of a business transition (e.g., merger, acquisition by
            another company, or sale of all or a portion of our assets), your Personal Information may be
            among the assets transferred.  You acknowledge that such transfers may occur and are permitted
            by this Privacy Policy.
          %p
            We may also disclose your Personal Information if we believe in good faith that such
            disclosure is necessary to (a) comply with relevant laws or to respond to subpoenas or
            warrants served on us; or (b) to protect and defend our rights or property, you, or third
            parties. You hereby consent to us sharing your Personal Information under the circumstances
            described herein.
          %p
            If you do not want us to use or disclose Personal Information collected about you in the
            manner identified in this Privacy Policy, you may not use our Site or Services.
          %p
            %strong The Ability Of Others To View Your Information
          %p
            If you choose to disclose Personal Information when posting comments or other information
            or content on publicly available portions of the Site (e.g., blogs), this information may
            become publicly available and may be collected and used by others outside of Optyn’s control.
            We will not have any obligations with respect to any information that you post to parts of
            Optyn available to others, and recommend that you use caution when giving out personal
            information to others through social media networks or otherwise.
          %p
            %strong Third Party Sites And Advertising
          %p
            The Site and Services link to other websites.  We are not responsible for the content or
            privacy practices of these other sites.  When visiting these sites, make sure you read the
            privacy statements for each site.
          %p
            This Privacy Policy applies solely to information collected by us through Optyn and does
